# Drawer Implementation Pattern

**CRITICAL: Drawers use query parameters (`d=drawer-name`) for URL-based state management, allowing deep linking and browser history support.**

## 1. Register the Drawer

In `src/hooks/use-drawer.tsx`, add your key and slug to `DRAWERS`:

```ts
export const DRAWERS = {
  // …existing entries
  your_new_drawer: "your-new-drawer"
} as const;
```

## 2. Create the Drawer Component

**ALWAYS use the Drawer component structure:**

```tsx
import {
  Drawer,
  DrawerContent,
  DrawerHeader,
  DrawerBody,
  DrawerFooter, // Optional, only if you have footer actions
  DrawerTitle, // Optional, for drawer title
} from "@/components/ui/drawer";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

type Props = {
  open: boolean;
  onOpenChange: (open: boolean) => void;
  // Add other props as needed
};

export const YourNewDrawer = ({ open, onOpenChange }: Props) => {
  return (
    <Drawer open={open} onOpenChange={onOpenChange}>
      <DrawerContent side="right" width="70%"> {/* Use: "left" | "right" | "top" | "bottom" */}
        <DrawerHeader>
          <DrawerTitle>Your Drawer Title</DrawerTitle>
          {/* Optional header content */}
        </DrawerHeader>

        <DrawerBody>
          {/* Your drawer content here */}
        </DrawerBody>

        {/* Optional footer - only include if you have action buttons */}
        <DrawerFooter>
          {/* Footer content with buttons */}
        </DrawerFooter>
      </DrawerContent>
    </Drawer>
  );
};

export default YourNewDrawer;
```

**For drawers WITH data:**

```tsx
import {
  Drawer,
  DrawerContent,
  DrawerHeader,
  DrawerBody,
  DrawerFooter,
} from "@/components/ui/drawer";
import { useDrawers } from "@/hooks/use-drawer";

type Props = {
  open: boolean;
  onOpenChange: (open: boolean) => void;
};

export const YourNewDrawer = ({ open, onOpenChange }: Props) => {
  const { your_new_drawer } = useDrawers();
  const drawerData = your_new_drawer.data;

  return (
    <Drawer open={open} onOpenChange={onOpenChange}>
      <DrawerContent side="right" width="70%">
        <DrawerHeader>
          <DrawerTitle>Your Drawer Title</DrawerTitle>
        </DrawerHeader>

        <DrawerBody>
          {/* Access drawer data via `drawerData` */}
          {drawerData && <div>Received: {JSON.stringify(drawerData)}</div>}
        </DrawerBody>
      </DrawerContent>
    </Drawer>
  );
};

export default YourNewDrawer;
```

## 3. Drawer Content Props

### Side Options:
- `side="right"` - Opens from right (most common)
- `side="left"` - Opens from left
- `side="top"` - Opens from top
- `side="bottom"` - Opens from bottom

### Width/Height:
- For `side="left"` or `side="right"`: Use `width` prop (string like `"70%"` or number like `500`)
- For `side="top"` or `side="bottom"`: Use `height` prop (string like `"400px"` or number like `400`)

### Common Patterns:

```tsx
// Right side drawer (most common)
<DrawerContent side="right" width="70%">

// Left side drawer
<DrawerContent side="left" width={500}>

// Bottom drawer
<DrawerContent side="bottom" height="400px">
```

## 4. Wire it up

In the layout or page where the drawer belongs:

```tsx
import { useDrawers } from "@/hooks/use-drawer";
import YourNewDrawer from "@/components/your-new-drawer";

const SomePage = () => {
  const { your_new_drawer } = useDrawers();

  return (
    <>
      {/* …other content… */}

      <YourNewDrawer 
        open={your_new_drawer.state} 
        onOpenChange={(open) => your_new_drawer.toggle(open)} 
      />
    </>
  );
};
```

## 5. Opening & Closing Drawers

**Basic usage (no data):**

```ts
const { your_new_drawer } = useDrawers();
your_new_drawer.toggle(true); // open
your_new_drawer.toggle(false); // close
```

**With data passing:**

```ts
const { your_new_drawer } = useDrawers();

// Open with data
your_new_drawer.toggle(true, {
  data: { userId: 123, name: "John" }
});

// Set data without opening
your_new_drawer.setData({ userId: 456 });

// Access current data
console.log(your_new_drawer.data);

// Clear data
your_new_drawer.clearData();
```

**Using the convenience hook:**

```ts
import { useDrawerWithData } from "@/hooks/use-drawer";

const { openWithData, close, data } = useDrawerWithData("your_new_drawer");

// Open with data
openWithData({ userId: 123, response: apiResponse });

// Close drawer
close();
```

## 6. Query Parameter Management

**How it works:**
- Drawers use `d=drawer-name` query parameter to track state
- When drawer opens: `?d=your-new-drawer` is added to URL
- When drawer closes: `d` parameter is removed from URL
- This enables deep linking and browser back/forward navigation

**Special handling for campaign_details drawer:**
- Automatically adds `campaign=display_id` when opening with campaign data
- Automatically removes `campaign` parameter when closing

**Preserving other query parameters:**

```ts
// By default, other query params are preserved
your_new_drawer.toggle(true);

// To clear all query params when opening:
your_new_drawer.toggle(true, { clearQuery: true });

// To maintain history (use push instead of replace):
your_new_drawer.toggle(true, { maintainHistory: true });
```

## 7. Data Management

- Data is automatically stored in localStorage with key `drawer_data_{drawer-name}`
- Data is automatically cleared when drawer closes
- Data persists across page refreshes while drawer is open
- Data is automatically cleaned up when switching between drawers
- Maximum data size: 3MB (larger data will show an error)

## 8. Reading Data from Query Parameters

**For drawers that need to fetch data based on query params:**

```tsx
import { useRouter } from "next/router";
import { useDrawers } from "@/hooks/use-drawer";

export const YourNewDrawer = ({ open, onOpenChange }: Props) => {
  const router = useRouter();
  const { your_new_drawer } = useDrawers();
  
  // Get data from query params
  const itemId = router.query?.item_id as string;
  const drawerData = your_new_drawer.data;
  
  // Fetch data if needed
  const { data } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ["item", itemId],
    queryFn: () => fetchItem(itemId),
    enabled: !!itemId && open,
  });

  return (
    <Drawer open={open} onOpenChange={onOpenChange}>
      {/* ... */}
    </Drawer>
  );
};
```

## 9. Complete Example

Here's a complete example following all conventions:

```tsx
import { useState, useCallback } from "react";
import { useRouter } from "next/router";
import {
  Drawer,
  DrawerContent,
  DrawerHeader,
  DrawerTitle,
  DrawerBody,
  DrawerFooter,
} from "@/components/ui/drawer";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { useDrawers } from "@/hooks/use-drawer";
import { useToast } from "@/components/ui/use-toast";

type Props = {
  open: boolean;
  onOpenChange: (open: boolean) => void;
};

export const ExampleDrawer = ({ open, onOpenChange }: Props) => {
  const router = useRouter();
  const { toast } = useToast();
  const { example_drawer } = useDrawers();
  const drawerData = example_drawer.data;
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);

  const handleSave = useCallback(async () => {
    setIsLoading(true);
    // Your async logic here
    await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));
    setIsLoading(false);
    toast({ title: "Success!" });
    onOpenChange(false);
  }, [onOpenChange, toast]);

  return (
    <Drawer open={open} onOpenChange={onOpenChange}>
      <DrawerContent side="right" width="70%">
        <DrawerHeader>
          <DrawerTitle>Example Drawer</DrawerTitle>
        </DrawerHeader>

        <DrawerBody>
          <div className="flex flex-col gap-4">
            {drawerData && (
              <div>Received data: {JSON.stringify(drawerData)}</div>
            )}
            {/* Your drawer content here */}
          </div>
        </DrawerBody>

        <DrawerFooter>
          <div className="flex items-center gap-2 ml-auto">
            <Button
              variant="outlined"
              size="md"
              onClick={() => onOpenChange(false)}
              disabled={isLoading}
              type="button"
            >
              Cancel
            </Button>

            <Button
              variant="primary"
              size="md"
              onClick={handleSave}
              disabled={isLoading}
              loading={isLoading}
              type="button"
            >
              Save
            </Button>
          </div>
        </DrawerFooter>
      </DrawerContent>
    </Drawer>
  );
};

export default ExampleDrawer;
```

## 10. Best Practices

### Performance:
- Use lazy loading for drawer child components:
```tsx
const DrawerContent = lazy(() => import("./DrawerContent").then(m => ({ default: m.DrawerContent })));
```

- Memoize expensive computations and handlers:
```tsx
const memoizedHandler = useCallback(() => {
  // handler logic
}, [dependencies]);
```

### Query Parameter Handling:
- **Always preserve important query params** (like `p_id`, `from`, `to`) when opening/closing drawers
- Use `clearQuery: true` only when you want to reset the entire query state
- For campaign_details drawer, the `campaign` param is automatically managed

### Data Fetching:
- Use query params as the primary source of truth for drawer data
- Fall back to localStorage data if query params are not available
- Always check if drawer is open before fetching data: `enabled: open && !!itemId`

### State Management:
- Use drawer data from `useDrawers()` hook for passing data
- Use query params for IDs or identifiers that should be in the URL
- Clear local state when drawer closes or when relevant query params change

## Key Rules Summary

✅ **ALWAYS:**
- Use `Drawer`, `DrawerContent`, `DrawerHeader`, `DrawerBody`, `DrawerFooter` from `@/components/ui/drawer`
- Register drawer in `DRAWERS` constant in `use-drawer.tsx`
- Use `useDrawers()` hook to manage drawer state
- Use query parameters (`d=drawer-name`) for URL-based state
- Preserve important query params (like `p_id`) when opening/closing
- Use `side="right"` with `width="70%"` for most drawers
- Check `open` prop before fetching data
- Clear data when drawer closes

❌ **NEVER:**
- Use local state for drawer open/close (always use `useDrawers()` hook)
- Remove important query params (like `p_id`, `from`, `to`) when opening drawers
- Fetch data unconditionally (always check `open` and required params)
- Store large data (>3MB) in drawer data
- Use `Dialog` components for drawer-like UI (use `Drawer` instead)

## Differences from Modals

| Feature | Modals | Drawers |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Query Param | `m=modal-name` | `d=drawer-name` |
| Hook | `useModals()` | `useDrawers()` |
| Component | `ModalRoot`, `ModalContent` | `Drawer`, `DrawerContent` |
| Position | Centered overlay | Side panel (left/right/top/bottom) |
| Use Case | Forms, confirmations | Details, settings, side panels |
